# Define the Transcript Redaction Boundary

## Step

Transcripts contain secrets, tokens, customer content, and third-party
text. Observation pages are publications (rendered on the paper). Define the
redaction pass the distiller MUST apply — reuse the wiki's redact.ts
patterns or a shared library? — plus enforcement point (before persistence,
per the privacy resolution: never store what can't be shown) and what the
secure-mode masking marks in observation pages. Inherits, does not reopen,
the closed privacy boundaries ticket.

## Resolution (2026-07-12, grilled with Joel)

1. **Coverage**: observational memory covers ALL work — no domain is
   skipped. Sensitive-domain sessions (support inbox/customer content,
   health/TRT, family) get full observation pages with `privacy: sensitive`
   frontmatter: written to the Brain, recallable locally, NEVER rendered on
   the paper (renderer exclusion verified live 2026-07-12). Classification
   rides cwd/repos + a distiller judgment field; doubt marks sensitive —
   doubt costs a rendered page, never a leak.
2. **Secrets never persist, rendered or not** (Joel: committing to
   dark-wizard "is still kind of publishing"). Mandatory secret-scan (key
   patterns + high-entropy strings) over every distilled page BEFORE write.
   Scan hit → one stricter-prompt retry → skip with a tombstone line in the
   day's observation index. Never negotiate with the scanner.
3. **Inference is local** (ds4-central), so raw transcripts never leave
   flagg for distillation; the enforcement point is persistence. The wiki's
   redact.ts patterns get reused/shared for excerpt handling inside pages.

Unblocks prototype-observer-distillation (last gate).
